WEBVTT

00:02.400 --> 00:05.631
Hey, Cheers is filmed
before a live studio audience.

00:10.400 --> 00:12.709
Miss Chambers,
can I ask you something?

00:12.880 --> 00:14.074
You're a girl, right?

00:14.240 --> 00:16.276
Well, I'm a woman.

00:16.440 --> 00:18.192
Well, that's close enough.

00:18.360 --> 00:19.839
You see, in about five minutes

00:20.000 --> 00:22.673
I'm going out on my first date
with a city girl,

00:22.840 --> 00:24.637
and I'm really nervous about it.

00:24.800 --> 00:26.597
You know, I'm afraid I might
get tongue-tied

00:26.760 --> 00:29.513
and make a fool of myself.

00:30.160 --> 00:33.994
I don't want that to get in the way
of me picking up the babes.

00:35.360 --> 00:37.032
Et tu, Woody?

00:37.200 --> 00:39.350
After only a few months
here at Cheers,

00:39.520 --> 00:42.080
you're starting to talk
like the other reprobates.

00:42.280 --> 00:45.317
Well, thanks, Miss Chambers,
but, you know...

00:46.240 --> 00:50.028
...that's not enough. I wanna be
smooth with the ladies like Sam.

00:50.480 --> 00:53.313
Well, I think I can help you out.
Have a seat.

00:53.800 --> 00:57.031
A good conversationalist
is usually a good listener.

00:57.240 --> 01:00.755
I've found that people love
to talk about themselves.

01:00.920 --> 01:02.592
- Really?
- Oh, yes.

01:02.760 --> 01:06.594
People have an endless fascination
with their own little world.

01:06.760 --> 01:09.399
It's an observation I made
as a small child,

01:09.560 --> 01:11.551
although I've never understood
why it holds true.

01:11.760 --> 01:15.639
I, myself, have always found many
more interesting topics to talk about.

01:15.800 --> 01:20.590
Of course, I've always made it a point
to broaden my horizons.

01:20.800 --> 01:22.552
As a matter of fact,

01:22.720 --> 01:25.792
I was reading the New York Times
at the age of 4.

01:26.200 --> 01:28.998
And from then, on to the classics.

01:29.160 --> 01:32.835
Of course, it caused some hardships
as a youngster,

01:33.000 --> 01:36.913
always being far and away
the brightest in the class.

01:37.080 --> 01:38.991
Usually, the brightest in the class

01:39.160 --> 01:44.598
is regarded as some sort of
a pimply faced egghead.

01:45.680 --> 01:48.638
I'm sorry, Clifford,
what was your question again?

